		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: puNES Emulator (ex Fnes)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Can I recommend pre-scaling by a factor of 2 in each dimension, then applying bi-linear filtering? This serves to help non-integral scaling factors still look crisp, but not have such uneven-looking pixels. Plain bi-linear filtering looks too soft and ruins small lines and dots, so such a feature would give a nice appearance.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


